    shabd:transliteration "Dharam rāe hai har kā kīā, har jan sevak neṛ na āvai."@en-Latn ;
    shabd:translationEn "Dharam Rai, the judge, is created by the Lord; he does not come near the Lord’s devotees."@en ;
    shabd:hasTheme shabd:Karma ;
    shabd:commentaryKeypoint "Dharam Rai, representing karmic judgment, is merely a servant of the Divine and has no claim over those whom the Lord embraces as His own devotees."@en ;
